,"options":[{"id":"a","text":"Always, for any response"},{"id":"b","text":"Only when the RFQ is not Awarded/Cancelled/Expired and that response's status is Received","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Only when the response status is Pending"},{"id":"d","text":"Only after the response deadline has passed"}],"explanation":"Award appears only when the RFQ can still be awarded (not already Awarded, Cancelled, or Expired) and the specific response has been Received — meaning a quote was recorded for it."},{"id":"pu8","text":"Which feature does awarding an RFQ generate?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"A vendor bill"},{"id":"b","text":"A Purchase Order, linked back to the RFQ","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"A sales order"},{"id":"d","text":"A shipment"}],"explanation":"Awarding is the only action that creates a Purchase Order from an RFQ. The generated PO is linked back to the RFQ and reachable from the View PO link and the Generated PO field."},{"id":"pu9","text":"What is required to save a new RFQ?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"A part, a quantity of at least 1, and a required date","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"A part, a vendor, and a unit price"},{"id":"c","text":"Only a part"},{"id":"d","text":"A part, a response deadline, and special instructions"}],"explanation":"Required fields are Part, Quantity (minimum 1), and Required Date. Response Deadline, Description, and Special Instructions are optional. Save is disabled until the form is valid."},{"id":"pu10","text":"After you award a winning vendor, what status do the other vendors' responses get?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"They stay Pending"},{"id":"b","text":"They are set to Not Awarded automatically","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"They are deleted"},{"id":"d","text":"They are set to Declined"}],"explanation":"On award, the winning response becomes Awarded (green) and every other response on the RFQ becomes Not Awarded (amber), set automatically by the award action."},{"id":"pu11","text":"How do you compare vendors before awarding?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Open each vendor record and check its catalog"},{"id":"b","text":"Open the request and review the vendor replies side by side — each quote's price, lead time, minimum order, and tooling","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Export the RFQ to a spreadsheet — there is no in-app comparison"},{"id":"d","text":"Comparison is only possible after the PO is created"}],"explanation":"An open request shows every vendor's quote side by side — price, lead time, minimum order, and tooling cost — so you can compare them directly, then award the winner."},{"id":"pu12","text":"What does the 'Received' count column on the RFQ list tell you?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"How many units have been delivered"},{"id":"b","text":"How many of the invited vendors have responded with a quote","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"How many POs were generated"},{"id":"d","text":"How many days until the deadline"}],"explanation":"The list shows a Vendors count (how many vendors were invited) and a Received count (how many of them have responded). Together they tell you the response progress at a glance."}]}"""
